	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all it's my pic.&nbsp;&nbsp;Second of all I was estatic to have this and I'll tell you why.  I play on RALLOS.  Almost everyone on Rallos will take no drop ANYTHING with stats for general questing.  We all have 2 sets of gear, everyday gear, and maximum stats gear.  This is everyday wear. When you can have people take your gear it's a whole differant ball game.  Now I admit there are better things out there.  But this stuff gives a lvl 30 character a real chance to be outfited in no drop without the help of a group of 50's protecting him while he loots some rotting stuff from SS.  I have a bracer that is much better than this, but it's not NO DROP and I could not easily or cheaply replace it.  So when I am doing my genral moving around and grouping I wear my 9 pieces of NO DROP and only put on my best gear when I am not very likly to get jumped.  You never know who wants what and who will pay what to get something.  So stop staying stuff is crap because you friends guild has already twinked you out.  Some of us actully play the game the way it is supposed to be played.<br><br>And if anyone has a problem with this . . . come to Rallos and you can beat an apology out of me.  ;p<br>&nbsp;<br>Druid Serving Tunare<br>Rallos Zek</td></tr>
